olive oil
1 cucumber
1 tin sweetcorn
1 packet plant-based mince
1 packet tomato paste
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
½ cup water
1 tsp brown sugar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Plant-Based Mayo

• Thinly sllice cucumber.
• Drain sweetcorn.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook plant-based mince and sweetcorn, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• SPICY! The spice blend is mild, but use less if you're sensitive to heat. Add tomato paste and Tex-Mex spice blend and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the water and brown sugar and simmer until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.

• Meanwhile, microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.
• Combine shredded cabbage mix and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a medium bowl.

• Top tortillas with slaw, Tex-Mex plant-based mince and cucumber.
• Drizzle over plant-based mayo to serve. Enjoy!